thread.title: Grace Christian gets going from kickoff
thread.title_full: Grace Christian gets going from kickoff - PrepXtra Story

author: News Sentinel staff
title: Grace Christian gets going from kickoff
text:
Grace Christian was off and running right from the start Friday night.
Colt Treischmann returned the opening kickoff 96 yards to kick-start a 19-point first quarter and a 46-20 victory over Sweetwater in Region 2-2A.
Although Grace is 4-4, the Rams remained unbeaten in the region at 4-0.
Austin Kirby had a hand in three Rams touchdowns. He threw touchdown passes of 33 yards to Jimmy Clevenger and 22 yards to Ben Andrews, sandwiched around his 27-yard scoring run.
Clevenger later caught a 20-yard scoring pass from Luke Kirby.
Ashande Paxton ran 10 yards for a touchdown for Sweetwater (3-5, 3-2) and threw a 10-yard scoring pass to Brent Spurgeon.
Fulton 73, Union County 0: Fulton scored 46 points in the first quarter alone against overmatched Union County in the 2-4A game.
A pair of defensive touchdowns contributed to the early onslaught. Shaton Mobley returned a fumble 19 yards and Jarien Green scored on a 24-yard interception return.
J'Coryan Anderson later returned a fumble 7 yards for another touchdown for Fulton (7-1, 4-0), which held Union County (0-8, 0-4) to minus-11 yards of offense.
On offense, DaShaun McKinney caught a 33-yard scoring pass. He also returned a kickoff 80 yards.
Morristown West 50, Daniel Boone 7: Calvin Smith scored on offense and defense for the Trojans (7-1, 4-0) in the Region 1-5A rout.
Smith started the scoring by catching an 80-yard touchdown pass from Aaron Jones. He later returned an interception 32 yards.
DeAndre Delaney scored on runs covering 60 and 65 yards. Jones threw a second TD pass, 12 yards to Dawson Stanton.
Mouin Tannous scored on a 1-yard run for Daniel Boone (0-8, 0-4).
Gatlinburg-Pittman 42, Happy Valley 36: Austin Cline's third touchdown, a 24-yard run in the fourth quarter, turned out to be the difference for the Highlanders (4-4).
Cline, who ran for 127 yards, also scored on a pair of 5-yard runs.
Albert Werner ran for two G-P touchdowns and threw a 46-yard scoring pass to Collin Garza.
Sage Haun threw four TD passes to Josh Hammonds for Happy Valley (4-4). The scoring pass plays covered 36, 55, 66 and 48 yards..
Scott 42, Loudon 6: Billy Hall and Austin Chambers combined for two touchdowns to start Scott's 2-3A victory.
Hall threw TD passes of 84 and 11 yards to Chambers. Hall added another scoring pass and two touchdown runs for Scott (4-5, 1-3).
Brody Houston had a 2-yard scoring run for Loudon (2-6, 0-4).
